(1, 'pizza', 'en-gb', 'a dish of Italian origin, consisting of a flat round base of dough baked with a topping of tomatoes and cheese, typically with added meat, fish, or vegetables', 'http://audio.oxforddictionaries.com/en/mp3/pizza_gb_1.mp3', '?pi?ts?', 'dish of Italian origin, consisting of flat round base of dough baked with topping of tomatoes and cheese', 'a cheese and tomato pizza', 'Italian, literally ‘pie’', 'Noun', '19/02'),
(2, 'Concupiscence', 'en-gb', 'strong sexual desire; lust', 'https://audio.oxforddictionaries.com/en/mp3/xconcupiscence_gb_1.mp3', 'k?n?kju?p?s(?)ns', 'strong sexual desire', '', 'Middle English: via Old French from late Latin concupiscentia, from Latin concupiscent- ‘beginning to desire’, from the verb concupiscere, from con- (expressing intensive force) + cupere ‘to desire’', 'noun', '01/01'),
