(4, 'Evanescent', 'en-gb', 'soon passing out of sight, memory, or existence; quickly fading or disappearing', '', '?v??n?s(?)nt', 'soon passing out of sight or existence', '', 'early 18th century (in the sense ‘almost imperceptible’): from Latin evanescent- ‘disappearing’, from the verb evanescere (see evanesce)', 'adjective', '03/01'),
